30/10/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Donor countries are meeting at The Hague on Thursday (30 October) to discuss 28m euros in financial assistance for the establishment of a war crimes department in the BiH judicial system. 
The United States is expected to secure approximately one third of the amount. 
The new entity is expected to assist the UN war crimes tribunal, investigate war crimes fugitives, and help handle local trials against suspects. 
(HINA, BBC - 29/10/03)
